Calculate Outcome Metrics Using Salesforce Flows (Pilot)

You can create Salesforce flows with your own outcome calculation algorithms to store results in the Patient Program Outcome Management data model. Once you create a compatible flow and add it to a record in Indicator Definition, the Calculate Indicator Result button appears on Indicator Performance Period records.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise and Unlimited editions with Life Sciences Cloud or Health Cloud license.

When: Patient Program Outcome Management is available starting in June 2024.

Who: This feature is available to users with the Health Cloud Starter (for Life Sciences Cloud) or Health Cloud Foundation (for Health Cloud), and Patient Program Outcome Management permission set.

How: Create a flow with the process type Indicator Result Flow and associate it with an Indicator Definition record. After the flow is added to an indicator definition, the Calculate Indicator Result button appears on Indicator Performance Period records associated with that indicator definition. Click this button to launch the flow that you created.
title: Pilot Feature: Calculate Outcome Metrics Using Salesforce Flows
